==English==
===Noun===
'''dibs ''(uncountable)'''''
#''(childrens' language)'' a claim to the right to use something exclusively or before anyone else ''first dibs''
#:''I have '''dibs''' on shotgun!''
#:''Who's got first '''dibs''' on the chips?''

===Etymology===
Since the early 19th century, of disputed origin. Possibly short for ''dibstones'', counters used in a game with the same name, or to from ''dib'' in the obsolote meaning "to tap". Could also be related to northern English [[dip]] "small depression in the ground" or a shortened version of [[divide]].

